<subSubSection id="0FCC6525FF9EFFE0FF2154D6FB48A36D" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="476936AEFF9EFFE0FF2154D6FB48A36D" blockId="4.[151,1437,721,1072]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FF2154D6FECDA2FD" bold="true" box="[151,274,721,747]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FE0454D5FCD0A2FD" author="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Ponomarev, A. V." box="[434,783,721,748]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="275 - 313" refId="ref9701" refString="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Ponomarev, A. V. (2020) Karakumosa gen. nov., a new Central Asian genus of fossorial wolf spiders (Araneae: Lycosidae: Lycosinae). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 127 (2), 275 - 313. https: // doi. org / 10.35929 / RSZ. 0021" type="journal article" year="2020">Logunov &amp; Ponomarev (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D64D2DFF9EFFE0FCAD54D6FC75A2FD" authorityName="Logunov &amp; Ponomarev" authorityYear="2020" box="[795,938,721,747]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Karakumosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FCAD54D6FC75A2FD" box="[795,938,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Karakumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="80D64D2DFF9EFFE0FBCD54D5FA43A2FD" authority="Logunov, 2010" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2010" box="[1147,1436,721,748]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Zyuzicosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FBCD54D5FB34A2FD" box="[1147,1259,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Zyuzicosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FB4554D5FA43A2FD" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[1267,1436,721,748]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="233 - 263" refId="ref9649" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2010) On new central Asian genus and species of wolf spiders (Araneae: Lycosidae) exhibiting a pronounced sexual size dimorphism. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, 314 (3), 233 - 263." type="journal article" year="2010">
Logunov, 
<quantity id="802E9B4BFF9EFFE0FAD254D6FA43A2FD" box="[1380,1436,721,747]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1053999999999995" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" unit="in" value="2010.0">2010</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having a biramous synembolus, an embolus with a prolatero-apical origin, the tarsi of all legs covered by scopulae and spinules, and a similar ratio of posterior/anterior row of eyes. 
<taxonomicName id="80D64D2DFF9EFFE0FCDA551EFC24A325" authorityName="Logunov &amp; Ponomarev" authorityYear="2020" box="[876,1019,793,819]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Karakumosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FCDA551EFC24A325" box="[876,1019,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Karakumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="80D64D2DFF9EFFE0FB3D551DFB24A325" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2010" box="[1163,1275,794,819]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Zyuzicosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FB3D551DFB24A325" box="[1163,1275,794,819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Zyuzicosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the median apophysis with an inner and an outer plate, a synembolus with 2 acutely pointed lamellae, venter of opisthosoma not black, longer epyginal atrium and absence of septal pedicle (
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FC8B5566FB54A36D" author="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Ponomarev, A. V." box="[829,1163,865,892]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="275 - 313" refId="ref9701" refString="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Ponomarev, A. V. (2020) Karakumosa gen. nov., a new Central Asian genus of fossorial wolf spiders (Araneae: Lycosidae: Lycosinae). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 127 (2), 275 - 313. https: // doi. org / 10.35929 / RSZ. 0021" type="journal article" year="2020">Logunov &amp; Ponomarev 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FCC6525FF9EFFE0FF715582FEC0A439" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="476936AEFF9EFFE0FF715582FEC0A439" blockId="4.[151,1437,721,1072]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FF715582FE90A389" bold="true" box="[199,335,901,927]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="80D64D2DFF9EFFE0FEEE5582FE38A389" authorityName="Logunov &amp; Ponomarev" authorityYear="2020" box="[344,487,901,927]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Karakumosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FEEE5582FE38A389" box="[344,487,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Karakumosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a recently described genus with 10 species named to date (
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FB125582FF0BA3D5" author="World Spider Catalog" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" refId="ref10125" refString="World Spider Catalog (2022) World Spider Catalog. Version 23.0. Natural History Museum Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 21 February 2022) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="book" year="2022">World Spider Catalog 2022</bibRefCitation>
). Members of this genus are large and fossorial spiders distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FC4755AEFBA2A3D5" box="[1009,1149,937,963]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FB3E55AEFAD9A3D5" box="[1160,1286,937,963]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FAA555AEFA46A3D5" box="[1299,1433,937,963]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FF2155C9FEC5A3FE" box="[151,282,974,1000]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FE9355CAFE49A3F1" box="[293,406,973,999]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FE1655CAFDE4A3F1" box="[416,571,973,999]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FDC755CAFD30A3F1" box="[625,751,973,999]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FD4B55CAFB95A3F1" author="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Ponomarev, A. V." box="[765,1098,973,1000]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="275 - 313" refId="ref9701" refString="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Ponomarev, A. V. (2020) Karakumosa gen. nov., a new Central Asian genus of fossorial wolf spiders (Araneae: Lycosidae: Lycosinae). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 127 (2), 275 - 313. https: // doi. org / 10.35929 / RSZ. 0021" type="journal article" year="2020">Logunov &amp; Ponomarev 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FBE355C9FA4FA3F1" author="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Fomichev, A. A." box="[1109,1424,973,1000]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="677 - 680" refId="ref9766" refString="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Fomichev, A. A. (2021) A new species of Karakumosa Logunov &amp; Ponomarev, 2020 (Araneae: Lycosidae: Lycosinae) from Tajikistan. Arachnology, 18 (7), 677 - 680." type="journal article" year="2021">Logunov &amp; Fomichev 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, the 
<typeStatus id="986D880CFF9EFFE0FE8A55F5FEB3A41A" box="[316,364,1010,1036]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="80D64D2DFF9EFFE0FE5855F6FC57A41D" authority="(Pocock, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[494,904,1009,1035]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Karakumosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medica">
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FE5855F6FD09A41D" box="[494,726,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Karakumosa medica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FD5255F6FC5FA41D" author="Pocock, R. I." box="[740,896,1009,1035]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="110 - 121" refId="ref10026" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1889) Arachnida, Chilopoda and Crustacea. In: Aitchison, J. E. T. (Ed.), The zoology of the Afghan Delimitation Commission. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, Zoology, 2, 5 (3), pp. 110 - 121, pl. 13." type="journal article" year="1889">Pocock, 1889</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
could either be in 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FBED55F5FB57A41A" box="[1115,1160,1010,1036]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Iran</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry id="3FC1763EFF9EFFE0FB1B55F6FAE9A41D" box="[1197,1334,1009,1035]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="23474B5FFF9EFFE0FAF355F6FECDA439" author="Zamani, A. &amp; Mirshamsi, O. &amp; Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Moradmand, M." pageId="4" pageNumber="505" refId="ref10170" refString="Zamani, A., Mirshamsi, O., Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Moradmand, M. (2021) The Checklist of the Spiders of Iran. Version 2021. Available from http: // www. spiders. ir (accessed 26 September 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Zamani 
<emphasis id="75A2EABCFF9EFFE0FF215211FF17A439" box="[151,200,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
